The paper deals with active learning for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of self-supervised learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes a new acquisition function, which involves optimizing the distribution shift between datasets, a topic that falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
